The relationship between the implantation dose and the maximum impurity concentration within the semiconductor film is discussed below.


When the dose amount is denoted by N0 (cm-2), the impurity concentration N(x) (cm-3) is given by:


N(x)=N0/(2 PI )1/2 ( DELTA Rp) * exp +-(X-Rp)2 /2( DELTA Rp)2 }

The dose of the LDD portion of the NMOS TFT in the shift register of FIG. 44 is 2 * 1013 cm-2.


Therefore, it can be seen from FIG. 45 that the sheet resistance of the LDD portion is 36 k OMEGA /.quadrature.. The parasitic resistance is calculated as follows:


Contact hole size=100  MU m2 ;


Contact resistance=1.2 k OMEGA ;


Resistance of the source and the drain portions=(length of source and drain portions / width of source and drain portions) * sheet resistance of source and drain portions=(7  MU m/14  MU m) * 530  OMEGA /.quadrature.=0.265 k OMEGA ;


Resistance of LDD portion=(length of LDD portion / width of LDD portion) * sheet resistance of the LDD portion=(2  MU m/10  MU m) * 36 k OMEGA /.quadrature.=7.2 k OMEGA ;


Overall parasitic resistance=(contact resistance+resistance of source and drain portions+resistance of LDD portion) * 2=(1.2 k OMEGA +0.265 k OMEGA +7.2 k OMEGA ) * 2=17.33 k OMEGA .

(2) NMOS (Comparative Example)


Contact resistance=1.4 k OMEGA ;


Resistance of source and drain portions=(7  MU m/14  MU m) * 2.6 k OMEGA /.quadrature.=1.3 k OMEGA ;


Resistance of LDD portion=(2  MU m/10  MU m) * 180 k OMEGA /.quadrature.=36 k OMEGA ;


Overall parasitic resistance=(1.4 k OMEGA +1.3 k OMEGA +36 k OMEGA ) * 2=77.4 k OMEGA .

(3) PMOS (This Embodiment)


Contact resistance=1.18 k OMEGA ;


Resistance of source and drain portions=(7  MU m/14  MU m) * 50 k OMEGA =0.025 k OMEGA ;


Resistance of LDD portion=(2  MU m/10  MU m) * 13 k OMEGA =2.6 k OMEGA ;


Overall parasitic resistance=(1.18 k OMEGA +0.025 k OMEGA +2.6 k OMEGA ) * 2=7.61 k OMEGA .

(4) PMOS (Comparative Example)


Contact resistance=1.4 k OMEGA ;


p+ source and drain resistance=(7  MU m/14  MU m) * 2.6 k OMEGA =1.3 k OMEGA ;


p- source and drain resistance=(2  MU m/10  MU m) * 375 k OMEGA =75 k OMEGA ;


Overall parasitic resistance=(1.4 k OMEGA +1.3 k OMEGA +75 k OMEGA ) * 2=155.4 k OMEGA .

(4.5  MU m-1.0  MU m)/10  MU m 530  OMEGA /3=0.062 k OMEGA ;


Overall parasitic resistance=(2.5 k OMEGA +0.062 k OMEGA +3.6 k OMEGA ) * 2=12.32 k OMEGA ;


ON-state channel resistance=15.56 k OMEGA ;


Ron=12.32 k OMEGA +15.56 k OMEGA =27.88 k OMEGA .

